==English==
===Pronunciation===
*krăk'ə(r), /ˈkrækə(r)/, /<tt>"kr{k@(r)</tt>/

===Etymological note===
The derogatory sense was originally applied by 18th-century cotton and rice planters to corn and wheat farmers, whose crops had to be ''[[crack]]ed'' before consumption.

===Noun===
'''cracker''' ([[crackers]])

# A piece of hard, salty, bread.
# Derogatory term for whites, often applied to financially disadvantaged Southerners.
# One who illegally circumvents protections in computer security to gain unauthorized access.
# A person who uses various techniques on computer software to defeat copy protection or add features (often cheat functions for games).
# A short piece of twisted string tied to the end of a whip that creates the distinctive sound when the whip is thrown or cracked. Also called a [[popper]].
# (usually plural) [[firework]]s.

====Synonyms====
*[[biscuit]] (1)
*[[hacker]] (3)
*[[white trash]] (2)
*[[popper]] (2)

